  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "JojwUEc/m3ylenr81BxmkgvTSok=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# never use fallback values with non-deterministic functions in reducers\n\nEven as a fallback, non-deterministic functions are forbidden:\n\n```typescript\n// \u274c FORBIDDEN \u2014 fallback is non-deterministic\nid: action.input.id || crypto.randomUUID();\ntimestamp: action.input.timestamp || new Date();\n\n// \u2705 REQUIRED \u2014 values must always come from input\nid: action.input.id;\ntimestamp: action.input.timestamp;\n```\n\nThe intent behind the fallback (\"provide a default if input is missing\") is reasonable, but the implementation violates [[reducer purity requires all dynamic values from action input]]. If the input field is required in the schema, the fallback is unreachable anyway. If it is optional, you need a deterministic default (like `null`), not a generated value.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
